'''''Stone of Sisyphus''''' is a 1981 video game developed by Chameleon Software for the [[Apple II]], [[Atari 8-bit computers]], and [[TRS-80]], and published by [[Adventure International]].

==Gameplay==
''Stone of Sisyphus'' is a solo dungeon adventure.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
Russ Williams reviewed ''Stone of Sisyphus'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 49.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last= Williams |first= Russ |date=March 1982 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=49|pages=34}}</ref> Williams commented that "I would say this is a good program and a reasonable game, but consider your financial situation before getting it."<ref name="SG"/>

